Here's what changed and how to fix each piece. .NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which has significant breaking changes:

---

### 1. `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` types removed (`OpenApiString`, etc.)

`Example` is now `JsonNode`, not `IOpenApiAny`. All `OpenApi*` primitive types are gone.

```csharp
// ❌ Old
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// ✅ New
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = "1.0";  // implicit JsonNode conversion
```

---

### 2. `Nullable` property removed from schema

OpenAPI 3.1 (the .NET 10 default) uses the `type` array instead. `Nullable` is replaced by the `JsonSchemaType` flags enum:

```csharp
// ❌ Old
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// ✅ New — strip the Null flag from Type
property.Value.Type = property.Value.Type & ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

Add `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;` (for `JsonSchemaType`).

---

### 3. `Reference` property removed from models — use reference proxy types

The `OpenApiSecurityScheme` no longer has a `Reference` property. Use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`:

```csharp
// ❌ Old
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference
      { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// ✅ New
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
operation.Security = [
    new OpenApiSecurityRequirement
    {
        [oAuthScheme] = scopes
    }
];
```

---

### 4. Collections no longer initialized by default

`Responses`, `Security`, `Properties` etc. may be `null`:

```csharp
// ❌ Old — assumed non-null
operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", ...);

// ✅ New — null-check first
operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
operation.Responses.TryAdd("401",
    new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });
```

---

### Full fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(
                    p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = "1.0";
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401",
        new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme =
        new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = [
        new OpenApiSecurityRequirement
        {
            [oAuthScheme] = scopes
        }
    ];

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type =
                    property.Value.Type & ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of namespace changes:**
- Remove: `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;`
- Add: `using System.Text.Json.Nodes;` (if using `JsonNode`/`JsonObject` explicitly)
- Keep: `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;`
